The paper deals with capacity regions of multiple access and interference channels with feedback and cooperation, which are topics related to information theory (cs.IT) and networked systems (cs.NI). The use of Gaussian channel models and noise variances also suggests a connection to signal processing (cs.SI) and multimedia (cs.MM). Finally, the concept of dependence balance is a mathematical tool that can be applied to various fields, including machine learning and optimization, which fall under the category of learning (cs.LG).
